quran[67]{c,v,t}:
  90,1,"No, I do swear by this city (Mecca)"
  90,2,and you are a dweller of this city
  90,3,and by the begetter (father) and that which he begot (son)
  90,4,We have indeed created man in hardship
  90,5,Does he think that no one will ever have power over him
  90,6,"He says, “I have destroyed plenty of wealth.”"
  90,7,Does he think that no one sees him
  90,8,Did We not make for him two eyes
  90,9,and a tongue and two lips
  90,10,and show him the two high ways (of good and evil)
  90,11,But he did not attempt the uphill (road)
  90,12,And what will make you realize what the uphill (road) is
  90,13,Freeing a slave
  90,14,or feeding during a period of hunger
  90,15,an orphan having relationship
  90,16,or the dusty poor
  90,17,then to be among those who believe and recommend to each other patience and recommend to each other compassion
  90,18,Those are the companions of the right hand (side)
  90,19,"And those who do not believe in Our signs, they are the companions of the left hand (side)"
  90,20,Fire will be closed over them (enveloping them from all sides)
  91,1,By the sun and its light
  91,2,and the moon when it reflects it
  91,3,and the day when it unveils it
  91,4,and the night when it covers it
  91,5,and the sky and Him Who built it
  91,6,and the earth and Him Who spread it
  91,7,and the soul and Him Who balanced it
  91,8,"then inspired in it, its transgressions and its guarding (against evils)"
  91,9,He indeed succeeds who purifies it
  91,10,and he indeed fails who buries it
  91,11,Samood denied (the truth) due to their rebellion
  91,12,when the most wretched of them broke forth
  91,13,"The messenger of Allah told them, “It is the she-camel of Allah, so let her drink.”"
  91,14,But they denied him and slaughtered her so their Fosterer destroyed them due to their sin and thus balanced it (the destruction was equal to their crime)
  91,15,And He does not fear its consequence
  92,1,By the night when it covers (the sun)
  92,2,and the day when it unveils (the sun)
  92,3,and Him Who created the male and the female
  92,4,Your striving is certainly for diverse ends
  92,5,So as for him who gave and guarded (against evil)
  92,6,and accepted that which was best
  92,7,We will facilitate him for ease
  92,8,And as for him who was niggardly and considered himself independent
  92,9,and denied that which was best
  92,10,We will facilitate him for difficulty
  92,11,And his wealth will not keep him safe from difficulty when he perishes
  92,12,It is certainly on Us to guide
  92,13,"And certainly, Ours is the latter (future) and the former (past)"
  92,14,So I warn you of the blazing fire
  92,15,None will enter it except the wretched
  92,16,who denied and turned away
  92,17,And one who guards (against evil) will be saved from it
  92,18,he who gives his wealth for his self purification
  92,19,"and he does not bestow favour on anyone, from that which is with him, (with the intention of) being rewarded (back)"
  92,20,"but he seeks the Attention of his Fosterer, the High"
  92,21,And he will surely be pleased
  93,1,By the brightness of the day
  93,2,and the night when it darkens
  93,3,Your Fosterer has neither forsaken you nor does he hate you
  93,4,And surely the latter period (future) will be better for you than the former (past)
  93,5,And surely you will be given (so much) by your Fosterer that you will be pleased
  93,6,"Did He not find you an orphan, then give you shelter"
  93,7,and find you wandering then guide you
  93,8,and find you poor then make you free of want
  93,9,So as for the orphan do not oppress (him)
  93,10,and as for the beggar do not drive him away
  93,11,"and as for the favour of your Fosterer, do proclaim"